 :tx/rationale "ADR-FOUNDATION-015: THE OBSERVER FORMALISM. Extractors are measurement operators, not plugins. Each extractor E_i projects reality onto a subspace: Store = union_i E_i(Reality). The epistemological horizon (gap between reality and store) is expandable by adding observers. OBSERVER AXIOM: every datom arrives through an observer — the store has no oracle. Three consequences: (1) observer completeness is measurable (missing extractors = missing subspaces), (2) observer quality is learnable (OBSERVER-4 calibrates extractor reliability), (3) the store reasons about its own observation capabilities (:extractor/* datoms). Observer lattice: observers ordered by refinement, join=union, meet=intersection, calibration navigates this lattice. Missing schema: source_category (what aspect of reality), expected_boundaries (which policy boundaries informed), observation_cost (time/compute/disruption), composition (how extractors combine). Scientific parallel: adding an extractor = inventing a new instrument (telescope, interferometer)."
